    "body": "### Problem\n\n The built-in LSP codelens renderer can trigger a `ModeChanged` event from Insert mode to Normal mode while Neovim still\n  remains in Insert mode.\n\n  This appears to be related to this code in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua`:\n\n  ```lua\n  -- Fix https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/16166\n  -- Make sure the code lens on the first line is visible when updating.\n  if row == 0 then\n    vim.cmd('normal! zb')\n  end\n```\n\n  When normal! zb is executed from an asynchronous callback while Insert mode is active, ModeChanged observers see an i:n\n  transition even though vim.fn.mode() later still reports i.\n\n  In my full configuration, this was first noticed through LSP codelens updates from tinymist. The visible symptom was that\n  mode-dependent UI state became inconsistent: the statusline still showed Insert mode, but a highlight updated from\n  ModeChanged changed back to the Normal-mode color.\n\n  I also saw input corruption while typing with codelens enabled. The first character typed appeared to stay fixed at the\n  end of the line while further input was inserted before it. I have not reduced that input corruption itself to nvim\n  --clean, so I am reporting it as a related observation rather than the minimal repro. Disabling codelens for the LSP\n  client fixed both the UI inconsistency and the input issue in my configuration.\n\n  Official nightly tarball from GitHub releases. Also reproduced with local NVIM v0.12.0 installation.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n  nvim --clean --headless +'lua\n  local events = {}\n\n  vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"ModeChanged\", {\n    callback = function(args)\n      table.insert(events, args.match .. \":\" .. vim.fn.mode())\n    end,\n  })\n\n    print(\"mode=\" .. vim.fn.mode())\n    print(vim.inspect(events))\n    vim.cmd(\"qa!\")\n  end, 500)\n\n  vim.cmd(\"startinsert\")\n  '\n```\n\n  The output includes an Insert-to-Normal ModeChanged event even though the final mode is still Insert:\n\n```\n  mode=i\n  { \"n:i:i\", \"i:n:n\" }\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n  Running a non-editing Normal-mode command such as normal! zb from an asynchronous callback while Insert mode is active\n  should not leave ModeChanged observers with a spurious transition to Normal mode while Neovim remains in Insert mode.\n\n  For the LSP codelens renderer specifically, rendering a first-line codelens should not cause ModeChanged i:n while the\n  user is typing in Insert mode.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-400+g14819d55fb Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A. This uses Neovim's built-in LSP codelens implementation (`vim.lsp.codelens`), which Vim does not have.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux / WSL2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A, reproduces with --headless\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n  Official nightly tarball from GitHub releases",
